<div class="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-3 lg:gap-8">
  <div class="lg:col-span-2">
    <div class="mb-8"><%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "leaderboard" %></div>

    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3 tracking-tight">Days Until Date Calculator</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8 leading-relaxed">Count down to any date and see the remaining time in days, weeks, months, hours, minutes, and business days.</p>

    <div data-controller="days-until-calculator" class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 md:gap-8">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div>
            <label class="block text-sm font-semibold text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-1.5">Target Date</label>
            <input type="date" data-days-until-calculator-target="targetDate" data-action="input->days-until-calculator#calculate" class="w-full">
          </div>
          <div class="pt-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Enter any future or past date to see the exact time difference from today. Works for event countdowns, deadline tracking, and historical lookups.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-amber-50 dark:from-orange-900/20 dark:to-amber-900/20 rounded-2xl p-6">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-5">Countdown</h2>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Status</span>
              <span class="text-lg font-bold text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400" data-days-until-calculator-target="resultDirection">&mdash;</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Days</span>
              <span class="text-xl font-bold text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400" data-days-until-calculator-target="resultDays">&mdash;</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Weeks</span>
              <span class="text-xl font-bold text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400" data-days-until-calculator-target="resultWeeks">&mdash;</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Months</span>
              <span class="text-xl font-bold text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400" data-days-until-calculator-target="resultMonths">&mdash;</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Hours</span>
              <span class="text-xl font-bold text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400" data-days-until-calculator-target="resultHours">&mdash;</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Minutes</span>
              <span class="text-xl font-bold text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400" data-days-until-calculator-target="resultMinutes">&mdash;</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Business Days</span>
              <span class="text-xl font-bold text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400" data-days-until-calculator-target="resultBusinessDays">&mdash;</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <button data-action="click->days-until-calculator#copy" class="mt-6 w-full px-4 py-2.5 bg-gradient-to-r from-orange-600 to-amber-600 hover:from-orange-700 hover:to-amber-700 text-white rounded-xl shadow-sm shadow-orange-500/20 hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-orange-500/25 transition-all duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-orange-500 focus:ring-offset-2 text-sm font-medium">Copy Results</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-8"><%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "in_results" %></div>

    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <h2>How to Use the Days Until Date Calculator</h2>
      <p>
        Simply select a target date from the date picker and the calculator instantly computes the time remaining in multiple units. You will see the total number of calendar days, the equivalent in weeks (with remaining days), total months, total hours, total minutes, and the number of business days. If you enter a date in the past, the calculator tells you how long ago it was instead.
      </p>
      <p>
        The business days count is especially valuable for workplace deadlines, delivery estimates, and project timelines where only weekdays matter. It excludes Saturdays and Sundays from the count, giving you the number of working days between today and your target date.
      </p>

      <div class="my-6"><%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "in_content" %></div>

      <h2>Common Uses for Date Countdowns</h2>
      <p>
        Date countdowns serve a wide variety of purposes in both personal and professional contexts. Couples count down to weddings, families count down to vacations, and students track days until graduation. In the workplace, project managers count business days to deadlines, shipping departments estimate delivery windows, and HR teams calculate notice periods and probationary timelines.
      </p>

      <h3>Event Planning</h3>
      <p>
        When planning an event, knowing the exact number of days helps you create a realistic preparation timeline. If your event is 90 days away and you have 20 tasks to complete, you know each task gets about 4.5 days on average. The business day count helps you plan tasks that depend on vendors, venues, or other businesses that operate on weekday schedules.
      </p>

      <h3>Deadline Management</h3>
      <p>
        Many legal, financial, and contractual deadlines are expressed in business days rather than calendar days. A 30-business-day deadline is approximately 6 calendar weeks, not 30 calendar days. This calculator helps you avoid the common mistake of conflating business days with calendar days, which can lead to missed deadlines and penalties.
      </p>

      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <h3>How do I find out how many days until a specific date?</h3>
      <p>
        Enter your target date in the date picker above. The calculator instantly shows the number of days remaining from today, along with the equivalent in weeks, months, hours, and minutes. It also shows the number of business days until the date.
      </p>

      <h3>Does the calculator show business days?</h3>
      <p>
        Yes. In addition to total calendar days, the calculator shows the number of business days (Monday through Friday) between today and your target date. This is useful for work deadlines, shipping estimates, and project planning.
      </p>

      <h3>What if the date is in the past?</h3>
      <p>
        The calculator works for both future and past dates. If you enter a past date, it shows how many days ago it was and marks the result accordingly.
      </p>

      <h3>How are months calculated in the countdown?</h3>
      <p>
        Months are calculated as whole calendar months between today and the target date. The calculation uses calendar months which vary in length (28 to 31 days), providing a natural way to express longer durations.
      </p>

      <h3>Can I use this to count down to an event?</h3>
      <p>
        Yes, this is perfect for event countdowns. Enter the date of your event and instantly see exactly how many days, weeks, and months you have to prepare. The business days count is especially helpful for planning work tasks that need to be completed before the event.
      </p>

